      "comment": "SILVER SQUEEZE (3) made a big impression on debut when flew the lids with a sensational early split and hit the frame with a 1.3 lengths second (22.77) over 388m at Gosford. Looks promising and can only be further improved. YEAH BUDDY (1) comes off an average run last start when fifth at this track over 320m behind Queen Kade (18.94). Strong form has emerged from his last run. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. SECRET BULLET (2) pinged the lids from out wide but run ended and faded out of it late when 7th at Gosford in Maiden company. Should be in this for a long way. MIDNIGHT KELLY (7) is still a maiden but is regularly in the top-three.",
